(9:31 AM case called.) Prosecuting attorney Monica A Fallon in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Nahusenay S Berhanu does not appear in court or via Zoom. Attorney William A. Schembera in court for Nahusenay S Berhanu.

Court advises Attorney Schembera may schedule with the Branch 1 Judicial Assistant and can be done via Zoom. 
(9:44 AM case recalled.) Prosecuting attorney Monica A Fallon in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Nahusenay S Berhanu in court. Attorney William A. Schembera in court for Nahusenay S Berhanu. 
Attorney Schembera advises the defendant is now present but can't locate plea paperwork. Court askes Attorney Schembera to step aside to collect his paperwork and come back in a bit.
(10:07 AM case recalled.) Prosecuting attorney Monica A Fallon in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Nahusenay S Berhanu in court. Attorney William A. Schembera in court for Nahusenay S Berhanu.
Victim/Witness statute complied with. Agreement has been reached and is recited by counsel.
Defendant pleads No Contest to Amended Count 1: Resist Officer - Failure to Stop Vehicle.
Defendant is advised of charges, maximum penalties, elements of the crime(s) and constitutional rights. 
Court accepts the defendant's No Contest plea and finds the defendant Guilty of Amended Count 1.  
Defendant makes a statement.

Court orders sentence of 10 days jail with Huber privileges which may be satisfied by completing 80 hours of community service. Defendant chooses community service. Provide DNA sample and pay surcharge and pay court costs. 1 day sentence credit. Any remaining charges including cases 22TR1333, 22TR1334, 22TR1387 are dismissed and read in.
